-- Banco Mercantil, BM&F Bovespa, Petrobras: Latin America Equity Preview
-- Andres R. Martinez
-- 2010-07-12T09:34:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/banco-mercantil-bm-f-bovespa-petrobras-latin-america-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  
 The  MSCI Latin America Index  gained 0.4 percent to 3,866.85
In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-traded class of
stock.  
 Brazil  
 Banco Mercantil do Brasil SA  (BMEB4 BZ): The Brazilian bank
based in Minas Gerais state sold $200 million of 10-year bonds.
The shares were unchanged at 12.9 reais when it last traded on
July 8.  
 BM&F Bovespa SA  (BVMF3 BZ): The owner of Latin America’s
biggest securities exchange sold $612 million of 10-year debt in
overseas markets. The shares rose 2 percent to 11.73 reais when
it last traded on July 8.  
 Petroleo Brasileiro SA  (PETR4 BZ): The state-controlled oil
company’s pension fund will invest in the Belo Monte hydropower
damn in the Amazon, an official with Cia. Hidro Eletrica do Sao
Francisco said.  
 Separately, Repsol YPF SA, Spain’s biggest oil company, and
Petrobras found evidence of oil in an offshore well in Brazil’s
Santos Basin, the Brazilian petroleum regulator said. Petrobras
rose 0.7 percent to 27.58 reais when it last traded on July 8.  
 Mexico  
 Grupo Mexico SAB  (GMEXICOB MM): The nation’s largest mining
company is seeking a seat on the board of airport operator
 Grupo Aeroportuario del Pacifico SAB  (GAPB MM) after buying a 10
percent stake. Grupo Mexico gained 0.2 percent to 32.26 pesos.
Aeroportuario rose 0.3 percent to 39.71 pesos.  
 Grupo Modelo SAB ( GMODELOC MM ): Anheuser-Busch InBev NV,
the world’s largest brewer, said it won a dispute over its
ownership of a 50 percent stake in Grupo Modelo, reigniting
speculation that it may bid for the rest of the Mexican
beermaker. The stock fell 0.3 percent to 63.75 pesos.  
